            "id": "0ad3fda5f3f4485fa7dc6",
            "questionText": "A group of amateur astronomers in the Northern Hemisphere observed that on June 21, the summer solstice, the Sun reaches its highest position in the sky at solar noon. Assuming that Earth's axial tilt is $!$23.5^{\\circ}$!$ and the observers are located at a latitude of $!$\\phi$!$ degrees (where $!$\\phi$!$ is a known value), calculate the Sun's maximum altitude at solar noon on the summer solstice. Provide a single numerical answer in degrees.",
